== 衍生影響 ==

=== 對電腦文化的影響 ===
[[Debian|Debian]]以及系统的[[進階包裝工具|進階包裝工具]]當中包含了「hello, world」安裝工具。用戶只需要於終端（Linux 系統的Terminal）輸入「apt-get install hello」便能夠安裝此工具及其相關部件。雖然看似沒用，但卻可作為測試工具使用。同時，這亦能夠向新用戶展示安裝工具的方法。對開發者來說，這個工具展現了建立[[.deb|.deb]]安裝工具的方法。這個工具，連同GNU Hello便成為了撰寫GNU程式的教學軟件。<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://www.gnu.org/software/hello/|title=Hello - GNU Project - Free Software Foundation|accessdate=2017-07-07|publisher=GNU Project|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140529011826/http://www.gnu.org/software/hello/|archivedate=2014-05-29|website=gnu.org|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

=== 對其他電子產品的影響 ===
雖然Hello World在[[單晶片|單晶片]]微電腦、[[现场可编程逻辑门阵列|现场可编程逻辑门阵列]]及[[複雜可程式邏輯裝置|複雜可程式邏輯裝置]]中不能展現出來，一盞細小的微型LED燈會代替Hello World的作用，以表示安裝成功、相關程式功能已實現<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.embeddedrelated.com/showarticle/460.php|title=Introduction to Microcontrollers - Hello World|accessdate=2015-05-19|date=2013-09-11|last1=Silva|first1=Mike|website=EmbeddedRelated.com|archive-date=2015-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522081938/http://www.embeddedrelated.com/showarticle/460.php|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://electrosome.com/blinking-led-atmega32-avr-microcontroller/|title=Blinking LED using Atmega32 Microcontroller and Atmel Studio|accessdate=2015-05-19|last1=George|first1=Ligo|website=electroSome|archive-date=2014-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141105123532/http://electrosome.com/blinking-led-atmega32-avr-microcontroller|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/Avr-Microcontrollers-in-Linux-Howto/x207.html|title=2. AVR Microcontrollers in Linux HOWTO|accessdate=2015-05-19|last1=PT|first1=Ranjeeth|website=The Linux Documentation Project|archive-date=2015-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502194301/http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/Avr-Microcontrollers-in-Linux-Howto/x207.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.se/blog/blogg-modesty-corex/first-altera-fpga-design/3.2|title=3.2 The first Altera FPGA design|accessdate=2015-05-19|date=2012-04-02|publisher=Realtime Embedded AB|last1=Andersson|first1=Sven-Åke|website=RTE|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150521222132/http://www.rte.se/blog/blogg-modesty-corex/first-altera-fpga-design/3.2|archive-date=2015-05-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hackaday.com/2014/04/06/cpld-tutorial-learn-programmable-logic-the-easy-way/|title=CPLD Tutorial: Learn programmable logic the easy way|accessdate=2015-05-19|date=2014-04-06|last1=Fabio|first1=Adam|website=Hackaday|archive-date=2015-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/201505